@page "/"

<h3>MEV Validation Demo — Blazor Web App</h3>
<p>
    This app compares the <strong>MEV (Microsoft.Extensions.Validation)</strong> source-gen path
    against Blazor's runtime fallback validator across three scenarios: attribute-only user
    validation, mixed async attributes + <code>IValidatableObject</code>, and
    <code>IAsyncValidatableObject</code>.
</p>

<div class="alert alert-primary">
    <strong>Key insight:</strong> Each MEV page uses a local <code>[ValidatableType]</code> model,
    while each fallback page uses the corresponding <code>SharedModels</code> entity. The UI and
    validation attributes stay aligned; <code>DataAnnotationsValidator</code> chooses the pipeline.
</div>

<h4>Scenario 1 — User (<code>[IsValidName]</code> + <code>[UsernameAvailableAsync]</code>)</h4>
